<p>We also got first looks at some of the new mechanics and powers coming in the expansion. In a gameplay trailer, Bungie showed off some of the weapons, locations, and abilities that players can expect from The Edge of Fate. These include a rocket launcher with a ricochet effect and an emphasis on Darkness abilities.</p><p data-embed-type="video" data-src="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qlylquFX6EE" data-width="100%" data-height="100%">          <iframe src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/qlylquFX6EE" height="100%" width="100%" scrolling="no" frameborder="" webkitallowfullscreen="" mozallowfullscreen="" allowfullscreen=""></iframe></p><p>The developer has also more details about the gameplay, narrative, and new mechanics of The Edge of Fate. That includes a look at a new <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/destiny-2-renegades-expansion-is-star-wars-inspired-and-gives-you-a-lightsaber/1100-6531341/" data-ref-id="1100-6531341">Star Wars-inspired expansion called Renegades</a> and <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/destiny-2-will-have-customizable-location-difficulty-with-next-expansion/1100-6531337/" data-ref-id="1100-6531337">customizable difficulty settings for locations</a>.</p>
  
                        
    
        
        
  
